The Hawks were acting on a tip off that a group of robbers were driving from the Eastern Cape to Durban. JOHANNESBURG Five suspects have been killed in a shootout with members of the Hawks on the N2 Freeway between Port Shepstone and Shelly Beach.The Hawks were acting on a tip off that a group of robbers were driving from the Eastern Cape to Durban. They found the suspects on Monday and tried to stop them.However, the men ignored the warning signals and instead opened fire on the police, which resulted in a high speed shootout.Hawks spokesperson Brigadier Hangwani Mulaudzi says: None of our members were injured during that incident, and currently we are still trying to ascertain whether this group was involved in any other criminal activity. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)